52   public void testInitialTypingScope() {

54   CodingConventions.getDefault()).createInitialScope(
55   new Node(Token.BLOCK));
56  
57   assertTypeEquals(ARRAY_FUNCTION_TYPE, s.getVar("Array").getType());
58   assertTypeEquals(BOOLEAN_OBJECT_FUNCTION_TYPE,
59   s.getVar("Boolean").getType());
60   assertTypeEquals(DATE_FUNCTION_TYPE, s.getVar("Date").getType());
61   assertTypeEquals(ERROR_FUNCTION_TYPE, s.getVar("Error").getType());
62   assertTypeEquals(EVAL_ERROR_FUNCTION_TYPE,
63   s.getVar("EvalError").getType());
64   assertTypeEquals(NUMBER_OBJECT_FUNCTION_TYPE,
65   s.getVar("Number").getType());
66   assertTypeEquals(OBJECT_FUNCTION_TYPE, s.getVar("Object").getType());
67   assertTypeEquals(RANGE_ERROR_FUNCTION_TYPE,
68   s.getVar("RangeError").getType());
69   assertTypeEquals(REFERENCE_ERROR_FUNCTION_TYPE,
70   s.getVar("ReferenceError").getType());
71   assertTypeEquals(REGEXP_FUNCTION_TYPE, s.getVar("RegExp").getType());

3336   public void testGoodExtends4() throws Exception {
3337   // Ensure that @extends actually sets the base type of a constructor
3338   // correctly. Because this isn't part of the human-readable Function
3339   // definition, we need to crawl the prototype chain (eww).
3340   Node n = parseAndTypeCheck(
3341   "var goog = {};\n" +
3342   "/** @constructor */goog.Base = function(){};\n" +
3343   "/** @constructor\n" +
3344   " * @extends {goog.Base} */goog.Derived = function(){};\n");
3345   Node subTypeName = n.getLastChild().getLastChild().getFirstChild();
3346   assertEquals("goog.Derived", subTypeName.getQualifiedName());
3347  
3348   FunctionType subCtorType =
3349   (FunctionType) subTypeName.getNext().getJSType();
3350   assertEquals("goog.Derived", subCtorType.getInstanceType().toString());
3351  
3352   JSType superType = subCtorType.getPrototype().getImplicitPrototype();
3353   assertEquals("goog.Base", superType.toString());
3354   }

7011   Node n = parseAndTypeCheck(
7012   "/** @constructor */function A() {}\n" +
7013   "/** @constructor \n @extends A */ function B() {}\n" +
7014   "/** @return {number} */\n" +
7015   "B.prototype.p = function() { return 1; }\n" +
7016   "/** @param {A} a\n @param {B} b */\n" +
7017   "function f(a, b) {\n" +
7018   " b.p();\n" +
7019   " if (a === b) {\n" +
7020   " b.p();\n" +
7021   " }\n" +
7022   "}");
7023   Node nodeC = n.getLastChild().getLastChild().getLastChild().getLastChild()
7024   .getLastChild().getLastChild();
7025   JSType typeC = nodeC.getJSType();
7026   assertTrue(typeC.isNumber());
7027  
7028   Node nodeB = nodeC.getFirstChild().getFirstChild();
7029   JSType typeB = nodeB.getJSType();
7030   assertEquals("B", typeB.toString());
7031   }

7203   /**
7204   * Type checks a NAME node and retrieve its type.
7205   */
7206   private JSType testNameNode(String name) {
7207   Node node = Node.newString(Token.NAME, name);
7208   Node parent = new Node(Token.SCRIPT, node);
7209   parent.setInputId(new InputId("code"));
7210  
7211   Node externs = new Node(Token.SCRIPT);
7212   externs.setInputId(new InputId("externs"));
7213  
7214   Node externAndJsRoot = new Node(Token.BLOCK, externs, parent);
7215   externAndJsRoot.setIsSyntheticBlock(true);
7216  
7217   makeTypeCheck().processForTesting(null, parent);
7218   return node.getJSType();
7219   }

8207   "/** @return {!goog.MyClass} */ " +

8218   public void testComplexNamespace() throws Exception {
8219   String js =
8220   "var goog = {};" +
8221   "goog.foo = {};" +
8222   "goog.foo.bar = 5;";
8223  
8224   TypeCheckResult p = parseAndTypeCheckWithScope(js);
8225  
8226   // goog type in the scope
8227   JSType googScopeType = p.scope.getVar("goog").getType();
8228   assertTrue(googScopeType instanceof ObjectType);
8229   assertTrue("foo property not present on goog type",
8230   ((ObjectType) googScopeType).hasProperty("foo"));
8231   assertFalse("bar property present on goog type",
8232   ((ObjectType) googScopeType).hasProperty("bar"));
8233  
8234   // goog type on the VAR node
8235   Node varNode = p.root.getFirstChild();
8236   assertEquals(Token.VAR, varNode.getType());
8237   JSType googNodeType = varNode.getFirstChild().getJSType();
8238   assertTrue(googNodeType instanceof ObjectType);
8239  
8240   // goog scope type and goog type on VAR node must be the same
8241   assertTrue(googScopeType == googNodeType);
8242  
8243   // goog type on the left of the GETPROP node (under fist ASSIGN)
8244   Node getpropFoo1 = varNode.getNext().getFirstChild().getFirstChild();
8245   assertEquals(Token.GETPROP, getpropFoo1.getType());
8246   assertEquals("goog", getpropFoo1.getFirstChild().getString());
8247   JSType googGetpropFoo1Type = getpropFoo1.getFirstChild().getJSType();
8248   assertTrue(googGetpropFoo1Type instanceof ObjectType);
8249  
8250   // still the same type as the one on the variable
8251   assertTrue(googGetpropFoo1Type == googScopeType);
8252  
8253   // the foo property should be defined on goog
8254   JSType googFooType = ((ObjectType) googScopeType).getPropertyType("foo");
8255   assertTrue(googFooType instanceof ObjectType);
8256  
8257   // goog type on the left of the GETPROP lower level node
8258   // (under second ASSIGN)
8259   Node getpropFoo2 = varNode.getNext().getNext()
8260   .getFirstChild().getFirstChild().getFirstChild();
8261   assertEquals(Token.GETPROP, getpropFoo2.getType());
8262   assertEquals("goog", getpropFoo2.getFirstChild().getString());
8263   JSType googGetpropFoo2Type = getpropFoo2.getFirstChild().getJSType();
8264   assertTrue(googGetpropFoo2Type instanceof ObjectType);
8265  
8266   // still the same type as the one on the variable
8267   assertTrue(googGetpropFoo2Type == googScopeType);
8268  
8269   // goog.foo type on the left of the top-level GETPROP node
8270   // (under second ASSIGN)
8271   JSType googFooGetprop2Type = getpropFoo2.getJSType();
8272   assertTrue("goog.foo incorrectly annotated in goog.foo.bar selection",
8273   googFooGetprop2Type instanceof ObjectType);
8274   ObjectType googFooGetprop2ObjectType = (ObjectType) googFooGetprop2Type;
8275   assertFalse("foo property present on goog.foo type",
8276   googFooGetprop2ObjectType.hasProperty("foo"));
8277   assertTrue("bar property not present on goog.foo type",
8278   googFooGetprop2ObjectType.hasProperty("bar"));
8279   assertTypeEquals("bar property on goog.foo type incorrectly inferred",
8280   NUMBER_TYPE, googFooGetprop2ObjectType.getPropertyType("bar"));
8281   }

8866   public void testObjectLiteral() throws Exception {
8867   Node n = parseAndTypeCheck("var a = {m1: 7, m2: 'hello'}");
8868  
8869   Node nameNode = n.getFirstChild().getFirstChild();
8870   Node objectNode = nameNode.getFirstChild();
8871  
8872   // node extraction
8873   assertEquals(Token.NAME, nameNode.getType());
8874   assertEquals(Token.OBJECTLIT, objectNode.getType());
8875  
8876   // value's type
8877   ObjectType objectType =
8878   (ObjectType) objectNode.getJSType();
8879   assertTypeEquals(NUMBER_TYPE, objectType.getPropertyType("m1"));
8880   assertTypeEquals(STRING_TYPE, objectType.getPropertyType("m2"));
8881  
8882   // variable's type
8883   assertTypeEquals(objectType, nameNode.getJSType());
8884   }

9868   private double getTypedPercent(String js) throws Exception {
9869   Node n = compiler.parseTestCode(js);
9870  
9871   Node externs = new Node(Token.BLOCK);
9872   Node externAndJsRoot = new Node(Token.BLOCK, externs, n);
9873   externAndJsRoot.setIsSyntheticBlock(true);
9874  
9875   TypeCheck t = makeTypeCheck();
9876   t.processForTesting(null, n);
9877   return t.getTypedPercent();
9878   }
9879  
9880   private ObjectType getInstanceType(Node js1Node) {
9881   JSType type = js1Node.getFirstChild().getJSType();
9882   assertNotNull(type);
9883   assertTrue(type instanceof FunctionType);
9884   FunctionType functionType = (FunctionType) type;
9885   assertTrue(functionType.isConstructor());
9886   return functionType.getInstanceType();
9887   }

9889   public void testPrototypePropertyReference() throws Exception {
9890   TypeCheckResult p = parseAndTypeCheckWithScope(""
9891   + "/** @constructor */\n"
9892   + "function Foo() {}\n"
9893   + "/** @param {number} a */\n"
9894   + "Foo.prototype.bar = function(a){};\n"
9895   + "/** @param {Foo} f */\n"
9896   + "function baz(f) {\n"
9897   + " Foo.prototype.bar.call(f, 3);\n"
9898   + "}");
9899   assertEquals(0, compiler.getErrorCount());
9900   assertEquals(0, compiler.getWarningCount());
9901  
9902   assertTrue(p.scope.getVar("Foo").getType() instanceof FunctionType);
9903   FunctionType fooType = (FunctionType) p.scope.getVar("Foo").getType();
9904   assertEquals("function (this:Foo, number): undefined",
9905   fooType.getPrototype().getPropertyType("bar").toString());
9906   }

10448   public void testTypeCheckStandaloneAST() throws Exception {
10449   Node n = compiler.parseTestCode("function Foo() { }");
10450   typeCheck(n);
10451   MemoizedScopeCreator scopeCreator = new MemoizedScopeCreator(
10452   new TypedScopeCreator(compiler));
10453   Scope topScope = scopeCreator.createScope(n, null);
10454  
10455   Node second = compiler.parseTestCode("new Foo");
10456  
10457   Node externs = new Node(Token.BLOCK);
10458   Node externAndJsRoot = new Node(Token.BLOCK, externs, second);
10459   externAndJsRoot.setIsSyntheticBlock(true);
10460  
10461   new TypeCheck(
10462   compiler,
10463   new SemanticReverseAbstractInterpreter(
10464   compiler.getCodingConvention(), registry),
10465   registry, topScope, scopeCreator, CheckLevel.WARNING, CheckLevel.OFF)
10466   .process(null, second);
10467  
10468   assertEquals(1, compiler.getWarningCount());
10469   assertEquals("cannot instantiate non-constructor",
10470   compiler.getWarnings()[0].description);
10471   }

10677   + " */\n"

10679   + "function g() { baz(function() { f(this.length); }, []); }",

10681   + "found : number\n"
10682   + "required: string");
10683   }

10938   private void checkObjectType(ObjectType objectType, String propertyName,
10939   JSType expectedType) {
10940   assertTrue("Expected " + objectType.getReferenceName() +
10941   " to have property " +
10942   propertyName, objectType.hasProperty(propertyName));
10943   assertTypeEquals("Expected " + objectType.getReferenceName() +
10944   "'s property " +
10945   propertyName + " to have type " + expectedType,
10946   expectedType, objectType.getPropertyType(propertyName));
10947   }
